The Special Ambassador shall have, and may discharge, the following duties:
Attend and observe various meetings, events, gatherings, functions and social occasions;
Share points of interest and provide information about Miami-Dade County;
Provide reports to the Board of County Commissioners upon request of the Board;
Provide his or her services and transportation at no cost to the County; and
Other duties, upon the request of a member of the Board of County Commissioners.
